    "name": "StableCoin-EarlyWarning-30d-iter5",
    "description": "APPROACH 3 iter5 — EARLY WARNING MODEL (6.7): 4-signal cascade — HALT at day 11, CLEAR by day 18.\n\nThe iter5 EarlyWarning model is the PRIMARY HALT TRIGGER in the GENIUS/MiCA mint gate.\n  EW_HALT_SIGNALS = 4 (all 4 must fire simultaneously)\n  HALT:    ewSignals >= 4  (all four breach thresholds simultaneously)\n  RESTORE: ewSignals < 4   (any one clears)\n\n4 VALIDATED SIGNALS (from 609 de-peg event research):\n  Signal              | Threshold | Lead Time | F1 Score | iter5 curve\n  Curve pool imbal    | > 15%     | 4.2 hrs   | 0.80     | peaks 42% day 15\n  Order book decline  | > 40%     | 2.1 hrs   | 0.70     | peaks 65% day 15\n  CEX outflows spike  | > 3.0x    | 6.8 hrs   | 0.69     | peaks 5.5x day 15\n  Social sentiment    | < -2.0z   | 8.4 hrs   | 0.63     | troughs -4.5z day 15\n\n30-DAY LIFECYCLE (MINT HALT AT DAY 11, RESTORE AT DAY 18):\n  Days 1-7:   ALL signals below threshold → NORMAL (0 EW signals)\n  Day 8:      curveImbalance crosses 15% → EW=1/4 → WATCH posture\n  Day 9:      orderbookDecline crosses 40% → EW=2/4 → ELEVATED posture\n  Day 10:     sentiment crosses -2.0z → EW=3/4 → HIGH_ALERT posture\n  Day 11:     \u2605 ALL 4 FIRE: cexOutflow crosses 3.0x → EW=4/4\n              CRITICAL cadence, MINT HALTED 🛑\n  Days 11-17: Peak stress — all 4 signals active simultaneously\n  Day 18:     curveImbalance clears first (< 15%) → EW=3/4\n  Day 19:     orderbookDecline clears → EW=2/4 → ELEVATED\n  Day 20:     CEX outflow clears → EW=1/4 → WATCH\n  Day 21:     sentiment clears → EW=0/4 → NORMAL\n              \u2605 MINT RESTORED (EW condition satisfied)\n  Days 22-30: De-escalation, NORMAL cadence restored\n\nKEY CHANGE vs stablecoin-1:\n  EW_HALT_SIGNALS = 4 (all 4 must fire — not triggered by any single signal)\n  Simultaneous firing on day 11 (not gradual)\n  Coordinated clearing sequence days 18-21\n  Defensive posture: NORMAL(0) | WATCH(1) | ELEVATED(2) | HIGH_ALERT(3) | MAX_DEFENSIVE(4)\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
